               <p>FRANCIS TADMAN. This umbrella had been left in my care, and was, on the 7th of October, on the one pair landing at my house in <placeName id="t18291029-160-crimeloc904">Leonard-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-160-crimeloc904" type="placeName" value="Leonard-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-160-crimeloc904" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-160-off902 t18291029-160-crimeloc904"></join>; I know nothing of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-160-person1283">
                  SUSAN 
                  AFFORD
               <interp inst="t18291029-160-person1283" type="surname" value="AFFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-160-person1283" type="given" value="SUSAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-160-person1283" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lodge with Tadman. The prisoner came to the house to bring me some coals - he was obliged to pass where the umbrella was; I missed it immediately he was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-160-person1284">
                  ANN 
                  BYRNE
               <interp inst="t18291029-160-person1284" type="surname" value="BYRNE"></interp>
